#* {{RQ:Birmingham Gossamer|chapter=I|passage=As a political system democracy seems to me extraordinarily foolish, but I would not go out of my way to protest against it. My servant is, so far as I am '''concerned''', welcome to as many votes as he can get. I would very gladly make mine over to him if I could.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To engage by feeling or sentiment; to interest.
#: {{ux|en|A good prince '''concerns''' himself in the happiness of his subjects.}}
#* '''a. 1729''', {{w|John Rogers (priest)|John Rogers}}, ''A Sufficiency adjusted and recommended''
#*: They think themselves out the reach of Providence, and no longer '''concerned''' to solicit his favour.
